Package: MLFS
Type: Package
Title: Machine Learning Forest Simulator
Version: 0.4.3
Authors@R: c(
  person(
    given  = "Jernej",
    family = "Jevsenak",
    email  = "jernej.jevsenak@gmail.com",
    role   = c("aut", "cre", "cph")
  )
 )
Description: Climate-sensitive forest simulator based on machine learning.
  It simulates key forest processes: radial growth, height growth, mortality,
  crown recession, regeneration, and harvesting. The method for predicting
  tree heights was described by Skudnik and Jevšenak (2022) <doi:10.1016/j.foreco.2022.120017>,
  and the method for predicting basal area increments (BAI) by Jevšenak and
  Skudnik (2021) <doi:10.1016/j.foreco.2020.118601>.
